President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Scott Soles of Texas as the Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Agriculture. Soles is a Certified Public Accountant with over 30 years of experience in financial auditing and consulting. He currently works as a Senior Special Financial Projects Analyst and has previously held roles at global Fortune 500 companies and accounting firms. Soles earned a Bachelor of Business Administration (Accounting) from Southwest Texas State University. In addition, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Paul Winfree, Heather Nauert, and Kevin R. Hanrahan as Members of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. Their appointments would last for the remainder of a 3-year term.